header: You must follow the instructions to predict soybean disease.
instructions: The data points used to predict soybean disease can be classified by the features seed discolor, leafspot size, stem, leaf mild, int discolor, shriveling, leafspots halo, and plant growth. A value of 0 means no presence, 1 is low presence, and 2 is high presence. Data points with a high value for seed discolor and leafspot size often result in diseases with values of 1, 12, 14, 16, and 17. If there are no issues with seed discolor, leafspot size, stem,leaf mild, int discolor, or leaf spot halo, but low presence of shriveling and plant growth, then the disease will have a class of 10. Meanwhile, if all values are set to 0 then the class would be 8. If leaf mild has a high value and other values remain low then the class will be 6.
